          "LessonTitle": "Lesson 2: Neurons and Activation Functions",
          "Content": "In this lesson, we will dive deeper into the building blocks of neural networks: neurons. We will learn about the structure and function of neurons, including how they process and transmit information. We will also explore different activation functions used in neural networks, such as sigmoid, ReLU, and tanh."
        },
        {
          "LessonTitle": "Lesson 3: Training Neural Networks",
          "Content": "In this lesson, we will discuss the process of training neural networks. We will cover topics such as forward propagation, backpropagation, and gradient descent. We will also explore common optimization techniques, such as batch normalization and dropout, to improve the performance of neural networks."
